      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OCTOBER RACKETEER (1) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 5.5 metres from the winner in second over 1780m at Redcliffe. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Meets a comparable field and he can grab that well-deserved win. WANDARY DELIGHT (6) turned in a poor effort by her standards last start when 19 metres away in seventh over 2200m at this track. Form prior to that had been solid. May need luck at some stage extracting from the inside of the second row. Meets a comparable field and she can turn in a much better performance. IDEAL TIGER NZ (9) must be considered after he finished runner-up over 2200m at this track eight days ago. ROSEANNE RUBY (7) is worth some thought as place chance despite her last-start ninth over 1660m at Albion Park on June 25.",
